    <title>What’s In A Name?</title>
    <id>https://tylercecil.com/posts/2020/02/13/reference.html</id>
    <link href='https://tylercecil.com/posts/2020/02/13/reference.html'/>
    <published>2020-02-13T00:00:00Z</published>
    <updated>2020-02-13T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <summary type="xhtml">
      <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
                Problems with Reference
        <br/>
                If two things are equal, they can always replace each
                other, no? Well, “the number of Godfather Movies” equals
                “3”. My friend Alison only knows the first movie. Why is
                it that I might say <em>“Alison thinks the number of
                Godfather Movies is 1”</em>, but I wouldn’t say
                <em>“Alison thinks 3 is 1”?</em>
      </div>
    </summary>
