    <title>Paratype</title>
    <id>https://tylercecil.com/posts/2014/05/01/paratype.html</id>
    <link href='https://tylercecil.com/posts/2014/05/01/paratype.html'/>
    <published>2014-05-01T00:00:00Z</published>
    <updated>2014-05-01T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <summary type="xhtml">
      <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
                An Actor Model for Monomorphisers
        <br/>
                A proof-of-concept experiment written in Go to
                understand static monomorphising. Given a program in a
                toy dummy language with a Haskell-like type system,
                Paratype will perform type inference and type checking.
                If type checking passed, it will generate a monomorphic
                code realization of the given program.
      </div>
